author: JASTIN AHMAD TARMIZI
title: Four die in Subang Jaya house fire
text:
Monday, 6 February 2017 | MYT 9:19 AM Four die in Subang Jaya house fire by jastin ahmad tarmizi 
PETALING JAYA: Four people perished in a fire which razed a double storey terrace house in Subang Jaya. 
A spokesman from the Selangor Fire and Rescue Department said the department was alerted about the incident at Jalan USJ 2/5A at about 5.30am on Monday. 
The spokesman said that all four victims were found dead in the house however they have yet to be identified. 
He added that two of the victims were found in a room while another was found in a toilet and the fourth victim was found in a separate room. 
He said that 80% of the house was completely burnt and that firemen managed to bring the blaze under control at about 6am.
